text: Right now, I just woke up after a nap, which is a little weird, but ever since I moved to Texas, I've been having trouble concentrating on things, and I remember starting tenth grade as soon as the clock hit four and didn't stop until it was done. But when I moved here, the lessons got a little more challenging, and there was a lot more work to be done, so I decided not to spend hours on it and just move on, but the thing was, I was always paying attention in class and just knowing it, and now that I look back, If I had worked hard and stayed on track for the last two years without getting lazy, I would have been a genius, but hey, it's all good. lt's too late to fix the past, but I don't know how to focus on the future. I just know that when people say they live on campus, they can't concentrate, It would be easier for me there, but unfortunately, I live at home under my parents'watchful eye and a little annoying sister who just complains and complains. I have to move, but I don't know how to say it. Don't get me wrong, I know where they come from and why they don't want me to move out, but I have to go away and be alone. The only thing they're asking me to do is to keep my room clean and help with business once in a while, but I can't even do that, but I have to, but I have enough money from the U.S. to live in a college or an apartment next semester, and I think I'll take advantage of it. I went to Sixth Street last night and had a good time. I haven't been there that long. Now I know why I love Austin so much. I'm responsible enough to have fun, but keep my priorities straight. When I live at home, I can't go out without them asking where?With whom?Why?When are you coming back?And all those questions.I wish I could be treated like a responsible person for once, But my sister ruined it for me, and she freaked out when she moved into college and ruined her entire career by partying too much, and that's the ultimate reason why they don't want me to have fun, but I'm not little anymore, and they're gonna let me go exploring the world, but I'm Indian, with Indian culture, I mean, in terms of meeting people or going out with people or partying or just having fun. My school is already difficult, but I think having more freedom will put more pressure on me to do better at school. That's what my parents and ultimately expect of me. It's been fun to write, I don't know if you get anything out of this writing, but it helped me get some of my thoughts right. So I hope you had fun reading it and good luck with TA's.
